laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Computed tomography scan of the chest
laboratory_examinations.findings: No obvious metastatic lesions were detected in the lungs, but a benign-appearing lytic lesion with a sclerotic margin was detected in the right scapular neck.
Demonstrated a 4.5 Â·5-cm expansile mass replacing the radial head and neck and extending into the regional musculature; the mass demonstrated bright enhancement.

laboratory_examinations.date: Two months after the initial scan
laboratory_examinations.findings: The appearance of a small fluid-density lesion in the supraspinatus muscle remained unchanged.
Showed a mixed lytic-sclerotic lesion of the right humeral neck, extending to the mid-diaphysis, with additional smaller lesions in the glenoid and acromion.
Demonstrated some resorption of the graft proximally; radial head and hardware remained in good position.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Comparison with earlier radiographs indicated changes, with some resorption of the graft.
